author: kotkov
msg: Following up on r1619105, tweak the situations when we would like to skip
the new revprop_caching_on_off() test and its expected outcome.
(revprop_caching_on_off): Tweak the conditions under which we want to skip
this test — now we execute it unconditionally for all FSFS filesystems.
With non-efficient or unsupported atomics, the filesystem would print a
warning, so handle it non-abortively.  Making assumptions about this
test XFail-ing with both svn_named_atomic__is_efficient() and
svn_named_atomic__is_supported() hugely relies on the internal
implementation details, and there is nothing good with that.  So we ...
